The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes an unsupervised approach for domain adaptation. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The approach also involves clustering and pseudo-labeling, which are common techniques in machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The approach involves exploiting the similarity of unlabeled samples, which can be seen as a form of unsupervised learning, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with domain adaptation, which involves adapting a model trained on one domain to another domain, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible sub-category as well.
